author: Adam Harvey
title: No request for Bali murder conviction against Sara Connor
text:
Map: Bali 
Prosecutors in Bali have not requested a murder conviction for Australian woman Sara Connor over the death of a policeman. 
Connor and British boyfriend David Taylor were facing the prospect of 15 years in jail if they were convicted of murdering police officer Wayan Sudarsa during a fight on a Kuta beach in August. 
But prosecutors had said Taylor should be jailed for the lesser offence of group assault causing death, which carries a maximum penalty of eight years in jail. 
Earlier prosecutors said Taylor had no intent to kill the policeman, and showed remorse for his actions. 
More to come.
